<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-128-260  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 128 260.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  Oct 16 1989 v3 n42 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Lawsuit tests fed discount agreements. (General ServicesAdministration, Data Translation Inc)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Smithmidford, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Justice Department filed suit, in late Sep 1989, against DataTranslation Inc for overcharging the General ServicesAdministration (GSA) by over $500,000.andP;  The suit alleges that DataTranslation violated the most-favored-customer agreement by notdisclosing all its discounting information as required by themultiple-award schedule program.andP;  The GSA has required since 1982that all contractors give it the same prices that the contractorsgive their best customers.andP;  The discrepancies in prices werediscovered in an audit of the company's 1985 Schedule A contracts.andO;The government is asking for $1.39 million in damages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Data Translation Inc. (contracts).andO;Ticker:    DATX.andO;Topic:     Government ContractsLegal IssuesPricing PolicyLaw SuitUnited States. General Services AdministrationUnited States. Department of Justice.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>